'''Ernesto Alexis Vega Rojas''' (born 25 November 1997) is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] or [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Toluca FC|Toluca]], which he [[captain (association football)|captains]], and the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
===Toluca===
Vega made his senior team debut on 27 February 2016 coming on as a  substitute in a home [[Liga MX|league]] match against [[C.F. Pachuca|Pachuca]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Alexis Vega, contento de debutar con Toluca|date=2 July 2021|url=https://www.vavel.com/mx/futbol-mexicano/2016/03/05/toluca/615106-alexis-vega-contento-de-debutar-con-toluca.html}}</ref> On April 5 he scored his first professional goal for Toluca in the [[Copa Libertadores]] against Ecuadorian club [[L.D.U. Quito|Quito]], the game ended 2–1 and Toluca qualified to the tournament's [[2016 Copa Libertadores final stages|Round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Alexis Vega, motivado por su gol en Copa Libertadores|url=https://www.telemundodeportes.com/mexico/alexis-vega-motivado-por-su-gol-en-copa-libertadores}}</ref> On 16 April, Vega scored his first two goals in the league against [[C.D. Veracruz|Veracruz]] in a 4–1 home victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/reporte/_/juegoId/439297|title=Toluca 4-2 Veracruz (16 de Abr., 2016) Análisis del partido|website=ESPN DEPORTES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/alexis-vega-una-promesa-mexicana-para-emocionarse|title=Alexis Vega, ¿una promesa mexicana para emocionarse? &#124; TUDN Liga MX &#124; TUDN|website=www.tudn.com}}</ref>

===Guadalajara===
On 8 December 2018, Vega joined [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]] for a reported fee of US$9 million, making his transfer one of the most expensive in the club's history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.futboltotal.com.mx/futbol-mexicano/liga-mx/alexis-vega-seria-presentado-con-chivas-el-sabado/2018/12|title=Alexis Vega sería presentado con Chivas el sábado|publisher= Staff FT|website= Futboltotal.com.mx |date=5 December 2018|language=es |access-date= 16 February 2019}}</ref>

After playing six games without any goals and going three straight games without any wins, on 16 February 2019, Vega managed to score 3 goals in the 3–0 victory against [[Clásico Tapatío|town rivals]] [[Atlas F.C.|Atlas]], his first career [[hat-trick]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fmfstateofmind.com/2019/2/16/18228091/chivas-earn-emphatic-clasico-tapatio-victory-3-0-atlas-behind-alexis-vega-hat-trick-highlights|title=Chivas earn emphatic Clasico Tapatio victory behind Alexis Vega hat-trick|publisher= Rafael Díaz |website= Fmfstateofmind.com|date=16 February 2019|access-date= 16 February 2019}}</ref>

Prior to the start of the [[2021–22 Liga MX season#Torneo Apertura|Apertura 2021]], Vega was given the number 10 jersey.<ref name="espndeportes.espn.com">{{cite web|title=Chivas: Vega será el nuevo número 10, Zaldívar hereda el 9 de Macías|date=21 July 2021|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/8934950/chivas-angel-zaldivar-numero-nueve-macias}}</ref> In May 2022, Vega extended his contract until 2024, becoming the highest paid player in the club's history.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/10326087/alexis-vega-renovacion-contrato-jugador-mejor-pagado-historia-equipoI | title=Alexis Vega se convirtió en el jugador mejor pagado en la historia de Chivas | date=6 May 2022 }}</ref>

===Return to Toluca===
On 17 January 2024, Vega's repeated disciplinary issues at Guadalajara led to his transfer to [[Toluca FC|Toluca]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/12678618/chivas-alexis-vega-indisciplinas-regresan-lista|title=Las indisciplinas, un mal recurrente en Chivas|publisher=ESPN México|language=es|date=13 October 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/13110720/alexis-vega-chivas-toluca-fichaje-clausura-2024|title=Alexis Vega regresa a Toluca tras cinco años en Chivas|publisher=ESPN México|language=es|date=17 January 2024}}</ref>

On 8 March 2025, after trailing behind two goals against [[Club Necaxa|Necaxa]], Vega scored a [[hat-trick]], finishing the match at 5–2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx/alexis-vega-elogiado-mohamed-hat-trick-necaxa-revancha|title=Alexis Vega anota tres al Necaxa y Mohamed se deshace en elogios|first=Editorial|last=Mediotiempo|date=18 September 2025|website=Mediotiempo|accessdate=18 September 2025}}</ref> Vega helped Toluca to win the [[2024–25 Liga MX season#Torneo Clausura|Clausura 2025 league title]], contributing an assist and a goal via [[penalty kick]] in the [[Clausura 2025 Liga MX final phase#Finals|finals]] against [[Club América|América]], for an aggregate 2–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45343938/toluca-end-liga-mx-title-drought-aid-mexico-gold-cup-run|title=Toluca end Liga MX title drought, now can they lift Mexico's Gold Cup run?|date=27 May 2025|website=ESPN.com}}</ref> At the end of the [[2024–25 Liga MX season|season]], he was the team's top scorer with 13 goals and 11 assists.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/liga-mx/alexis-vega-se-convierte-jugador-mas-caro-liga-mx-tras-ser-campeon|title=Alexis Vega se convierte en el jugador más caro de Liga MX tras ser campeón &#124; TUDN Liga MX &#124; TUDN|website=www.tudn.com}}</ref> He was included in the tournament's best XI and was awarded Best Attacking Midfielder and Goal of the Year by the league.

==International career==
===Youth===
Vega was called up by [[Jaime Lozano]] to participate at the [[2020 CONCACAF Men's Olympic Qualifying Championship|2020 CONCACAF Olympic Qualifying Championship]], scoring one goal in five appearances, where Mexico won the competition. He was awarded the Golden Ball for best player<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/olympics-qualifying-men/article/vega-earns-2020-cmoq-best-player-award-presented-by-scotiabank/|title=Vega earns 2020 CMOQ Best Player Award, presented by Scotiabank|publisher=CONCACAF|date=31 March 2021|access-date=31 March 2021}}</ref> and included in the tournament's Best XI.<ref name=CONCACAF>{{cite web|title=Ellos son los 4 mexicanos que encabezan el 11 ideal de Concacaf del Preolímpico 2021|date=31 March 2021 |url=https://soyreferee.com/futbolinternacional/Ellos-son-los-4-mexicanos-que-encabezan-el-11-ideal-de-Concacaf-del-Preolimpico-2021-20210331-0016.html}}</ref> He was subsequently called up to participate in the [[2020 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Revelan lista oficial de la Selección Sub-23 que acudirá a Tokio 2020|date=5 July 2021|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/selecciones/nota/_/id/8854207/mexico-sub23-convocatoria-jaime-lozano-tokio-2020}}</ref> Vega scored Mexico's final goal in a 3–1 victory over Olympic hosts, [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]], as they won the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament – Knockout stage#Bronze medal match|third-place match]] to win the [[bronze medal]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.tudn.com/futbol/futbol-olimpico-varonil/bronce-mexico-vence-a-japon | title=México gana el bronce tras vencer 3-1 a Japón &#124; TUDN Fútbol Olímpico Varonil &#124; TUDN }}</ref>

===Senior===
[[File:2022 FIFA World Cup Match 24, Argentina v Mexico - 02.jpg|thumb|Vega disputing the ball against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]'s [[Rodrigo De Paul]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]]]]
Vega made his [[Mexico national football team|senior national team]] debut on 26 March 2019, under [[Gerardo Martino]] in a friendly against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]], as a 78th-minute substitute for [[Javier Hernández]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[ESPN]]|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=532880|title=Mexico v Paraguay game report|date=26 March 2019}}</ref>

In May 2019, Vega was included in the provisional [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] roster<ref>{{cite web|title=Tata Martino Announces Mexico Preliminary Gold Cup Squad; Vela, Chicharito, Herrera, Corona left out|url=https://www.fmfstateofmind.com/2019/5/14/18534851/mexico-el-tri-concacaf-gold-cup-copa-oro-squad-final-list-preliminary-corona-vela-chicharito-herrera|work=Fmfstateofmind.com|first=Antonio|last=Tinajero|date=14 May 2019}}</ref> and was subsequently included in the final list.<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección Mexicana anuncia lista definitiva para Copa Oro 2019|url=https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/copa-oro/seleccion-mexicana-anuncia-lista-definitiva-copa-oro-2019|date=6 June 2019|work=MedioTiempo.com}}</ref> In the first [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup Group A|group stage]] match against [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]], he would score his first goal with the national team in a 7–0 thrashing.<ref>{{cite web|title=México 7-0 Cuba: goles, resumen y videos|url=https://www.goal.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico-vs-cuba-goles-resumen-y-videos/7vna2lpkd3rr15sa06pez53sm|work=[[Goal (website)|Goal.com]]|language=es|date=15 June 2019}}</ref> Mexico would go on to win the tournament.<ref name="Straus">{{cite web|title=Mexico Turns Tide, Wins Gold Cup Title Again vs. Wasteful USMNT|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2019/07/07/mexico-usa-gold-cup-title-dos-santos-pizarro-pulisic-berhalter|publisher=[[Sports Illustrated]]|first=Brian|last=Straus|date=7 July 2019}}</ref>

In November 2022, he was included in the 26-man roster for that year's [[2022 FIFA World Cup|edition]] of the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lista de convocados de la Selección Mexicana al Mundial de Qatar 2022|url=https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecadeportes/lista-oficial-convocados-seleccion-mexicana-mundial-qatar-2022|work=Tvazteca.com|first=Omar|last=Moro|date=14 November 2022|language=Spanish}}</ref>

In June 2025, Vega was included in Mexico's roster for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/copa-oro/nota/_/id/15272774/seleccion-mexicana-convocatoria-final-copa-oro-2025-lista|title=México presenta lista final para la Copa Oro 2025|date=4 June 2025|website=ESPNdeportes.com}}</ref> In the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup knockout stage|quarter-finals]] match against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]], he would score the first goal of the match in an eventual 2–0 victory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/735343|title=Mexico 2-0 Saudi Arabia (Jun 28, 2025) Game Analysis|website=ESPN}}</ref>

